%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20nutritionist%20who%20lowered%20his%20cholesterol%20through%20diet%20shared%204%20simple%20tips%20for%20eating%20more%20fiber%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rob%20Hobson%20sits%20at%20a%20table%20and%20smiles%20into%20the%20distance.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694969dc64858d02d2173d0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERob%20Hobson%20adds%20a%20bit%20of%20fiber%20to%20every%20meal%20for%20his%20gut%20health%20and%20to%20keep%20his%20cholesterol%20levels%20at%20bay.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Burton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERob%20Hobson%2C%20a%20nutritionist%2C%20started%20eating%20more%20fiber%20after%20learning%20his%20cholesterol%20was%20high.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHigh%20cholesterol%20levels%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%2C%20but%20can%20often%20be%20improved%20through%20diet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHobson%20has%20a%20'fiber%20cupboard'%20and%20adds%20something%20from%20it%20to%20every%20meal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-eats-high-protein-diet-without-ultra-processed-foods-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERob%20Hobson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20registered%20nutritionist%20based%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20found%20out%20his%20cholesterol%20levels%20were%20%26quot%3Breally%20high%26quot%3B%20in%20June%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20manage%20them%20through%20diet%2C%20focusing%20particularly%20on%20increasing%20his%20fiber%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20later%2C%20when%20he%20tested%20again%2C%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchickpea-recipes-to-lower-cholesterol-science-backed-advice-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echolesterol%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20improved%2C%20and%20he'd%20discovered%20four%20tricks%20that%20make%20eating%20more%20fiber%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECholesterol%20is%20a%20fatty%20substance%20the%20body%20needs%20for%20many%20bodily%20processes%2C%20but%20if%20a%20person%20has%20too%20much%20LDL%20or%20%26quot%3Bbad%26quot%3B%20cholesterol%2C%20it%20can%20form%20sticky%20plaque%20in%20their%20arteries%2C%20putting%20them%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-look-healthy-heart-disease-failure-stroke-inflammation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecardiovascular%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20reduce%20cholesterol%20levels%2C%20the%20American%20Heart%20Association%20recommends%20exercising%20at%20least%20150%20minutes%20a%20week%2C%20quitting%20smoking%20and%20vaping%2C%20maintaining%20a%20healthy%20weight%2C%20and%20eating%20a%20heart-healthy%20diet%20that's%20low%20in%20saturated%20fats%20and%20high%20in%20fiber.%20If%20these%20measures%20don't%20help%2C%20then%20statins%2C%20a%20medication%20that%20lowers%20LDL%20cholesterol%2C%20will%20likely%20be%20prescribed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHobson%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BUnprocess%20Your%20Life%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Low%20Appetite%20Cookbook%2C%26quot%3B%20already%20worked%20out%20for%20around%20an%20hour%20each%20morning%2C%20and%20ate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-look-healthy-heart-disease-failure-stroke-inflammation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminimal%20ultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20saturated%20fats.%20So%20he%20zeroed%20in%20on%20fiber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20at%20least%205%20to%2010%20grams%20of%20soluble%20fiber%20a%20day%20can%20help%20lower%20total%20cholesterol%20and%20LDL%20cholesterol%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Lipid%20Association.%20Quinoa%2C%20oats%2C%20avocado%2C%20sweet%20potatoes%2C%20carrots%2C%20and%20chia%20or%20flax%20seeds%20are%20good%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20Hobson's%20tips%20for%20seamlessly%20adding%20more%20fiber%20to%20your%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a4aa01f-6ea0-4848-8371-896ad3e1f530%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEat%20breakfast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHobson%20is%20a%20big%20advocate%20of%20breakfast%20because%20it%20lends%20itself%20to%20high-fiber%20foods%20such%20as%20oats%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20seeds.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20easy%20to%20get%20plenty%20of%20fiber%20in%20at%20that%20time%20of%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20two%20go-to%20breakfasts%20that%20he%20eats%20on%20repeat.%20The%20first%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquick-easy-high-protein-high-fiber-breakfast-every-morning-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreek%20yogurt%20bowl%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20berries%2C%20oats%2C%20and%20chia%20seeds.%20The%20second%20is%20overnight%20oats%2C%20which%20he%20makes%20with%20milk%2C%20protein%20powder%2C%20berries%2C%20honey%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20seeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216694455-4bae-4acc-a454-c4db8f5516a8%5C%22%3EFiber%20cupboard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20cupboard%20with%20shelves%20of%20seeds%2C%20beans%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20pulses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69496cd564858d02d2173d7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERob%20Hobson's%20fiber%20cupboard.%3Cp%3ERob%20Hobson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHobson%20created%20a%20%26quot%3Bfiber%20cupboard%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20kitchen%20that's%20packed%20with%20fibrous%20foods.%20He%20challenges%20himself%20to%20include%20something%20from%20the%20cupboard%20in%20every%20meal.%20%26quot%3BThen%20at%20least%20you%20know%20that%20you%20are%20making%20the%20effort%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20stocks%20up%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-ways-add-beans-meals-protein-fiber-private-chef-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elentils%2C%20beans%2C%20pulses%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wholegrain%20pasta%2C%20brown%20rice%2C%20as%20well%20as%20snacks%20like%20fruit%20and%20nut%20bars%2C%20rye%20crackers%20that%20he%20likes%20to%20pair%20with%20some%20cottage%20cheese%2C%20and%20seaweed%20thins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20always%20rooting%20around%20for%20stuff%2C%20and%20I%20just%20think%20having%20it%20all%20in%20one%20place%20is%20so%20much%20easier%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e599fc6-b8d1-4acf-8b7c-eeb1438c25f3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdd%20pulses%20and%20legumes%20to%20your%20meal%20and%20put%20the%20rest%20into%20a%20Tupperware%20in%20the%20fridge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20easiest%20way%20to%20add%20fiber%20to%20a%20meal%20is%20to%20pour%20half%20a%20can%20of%20beans%20or%20pulses%20into%20it%2C%20Hobson%20said.%20Just%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecipes-black-beans-to-reduce-inflammation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecup%20of%20black%20beans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20contains%2015%20grams%20of%20fiber.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20add%20them%20to%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMix%20some%20into%20a%20soup%2C%20sauce%2C%20or%20curry%2C%20or%20simply%20sprinkle%20a%20couple%20of%20tablespoons%20on%20top%20of%20a%20salad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20not%20using%20the%20whole%20can%2C%20decant%20the%20rest%20into%20a%20Tupperware%20and%20place%20it%20in%20the%20fridge%2C%20Hobson%20said.%20That%20way%2C%20they'll%20stay%20fresher%20for%20longer%20and%20be%20easily%20accessible.%20%26quot%3BThen%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20'I'm%20going%20to%20waste%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20tin%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22140201b5-2f70-454c-af06-f674067ade72%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeep%20the%20food%20you%20want%20to%20eat%20visible%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHobson%20recommends%20keeping%20the%20foods%20you%20want%20to%20eat%20in%20a%20visible%20spot.%20That%20way%2C%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20reach%20for%20them.%20%26quot%3BNuts%20and%20seeds%2C%20always%20keep%20them%20on%20the%20side%20so%20they're%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20that%20the%20foods%20you%20keep%20on%20your%20countertop%20could%20impact%20your%20body%20weight%2C%20a%20factor%20that%20can%20influence%20cholesterol%20levels.%20In%20a%202015%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F1090198115610571%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESage%20Journals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20at%20Cornell%20University%20analyzed%20the%20visible%20foods%20on%20210%20countertops%20in%20New%20York%20and%20measured%20their%20owners'%20BMIs.%20They%20found%20that%20those%20who%20had%20just%20fresh%20fruit%20visible%20weighed%20an%20average%20of%2020%20pounds%20less%20than%20those%20who%20had%20unhealthier%20snacks%20like%20candy%2C%20soda%2C%20and%20cereals%20on%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20your%20basic%20See-Food%20Diet%20%E2%80%94%20you%20eat%20what%20you%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Wansink%2C%20the%20study's%20lead%20author%2C%20said%20of%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you're%20not%20ready%20to%20make%20changes%20to%20your%20kitchen%20layout%2C%20Hobson%20said%20to%20stick%20to%20one%20basic%20principle%3A%20%26quot%3BMake%20sure%20that%20you've%20got%20a%20bit%20of%20fiber%20on%20your%20plate%20every%20day%20with%20every%20meal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-lowered-cholesterol-4-simple-ways-eat-more-fiber-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767424021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694969dc64858d02d2173d0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutr