22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eridiculous%20trope%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20a%20fun%20one%20that%20I%20enjoyed%20reading%20about%2C%20rather%20than%20questioning%20why%20our%20two%20main%20characters%20chose%20to%20lie%20to%20all%20their%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFunny%20Story%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20classic%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eromance%20story%3A%20Daphne%20and%20Miles%20have%20both%20been%20dumped%20by%20their%20respective%20significant%20others%2C%20best%20friends%20Peter%20and%20Petra%2C%20after%2C%20wouldn't%20you%20guess%2C%20Peter%20and%20Petra%20decided%20that%20%3Cem%3Ethey%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewere%20in%20love%20with%20each%20other%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeless%20and%20heartbroken%2C%20Daphne%20and%20Miles%20decide%20to%20move%20in%20together%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20an%20act%20of%20desperation%2C%20decide%20to%20fake%20date%20in%20order%20to%20make%20their%20exes%20jealous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20wrote%20in%20my%20Goodreads%20review%20for%20this%20book%2C%20'There's%20something%20about%20the%20way%20Emily%20Henry%20writes%20flirting%20that%20scratches%20my%20brain.%26quot%3B%20Daphne%20and%20Miles'%20banter%20is%20(almost)%20unmatched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20relate%20to%20Daphne%2C%20her%20insecurities%2C%20her%20interests%2C%20and%20her%20flaws%2C%20the%20most%20out%20of%20all%20of%20Henry's%20main%20characters.%20I%20also%20just%20love%20Miles.%20He's%20the%20sweetest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFunny%20Story%26quot%3B%20has%20also%20been%20optioned%20to%20become%20a%20movie%2C%20with%20Henry%20herself%20writing%20the%20screenplay%2C%20which%20makes%20me%20very%20excited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20not%20No.%201%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1.%20'Beach%20Read'%20(2020)%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22beach%20read%20cover%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69388c7e7ecd1d1da66339b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBeach%20Read.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EBerkley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeach%20Read%2C%26quot%3B%20Henry's%20first%20foray%20into%20romance%2C%20is%20also%20my%20favorite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20book%20lover%2C%20no%20pun%20intended%2C%20the%20premise%20of%20two%20dueling%20authors%20challenging%20each%20other%20to%20swap%20genres%2C%20is%20a%20fun%20one.%20People%20may%20think%20romance%20is%20easy%20to%20write.%20But%20it's%20far%20too%20easy%20to%20give%20readers%20the%20ick%2C%20veer%20into%20melodrama%20territory%2C%20or%20make%20your%20romance%20just%20too%20unbelievable%20(in%20too-good-to-be-true%20or%20toxic%20ways).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20I%20think%20Henry's%20ode%20to%20the%20romance%20writer%20resonates%20with%20me.%20I've%20read%20plenty%20of%20bad%20ones%2C%20but%20I%20bet%20January%20Andrews%20(our%20depressed%20heroine)%2C%20writes%20amazing%20ones%2C%20even%20if%20she's%20going%20through%20a%20crisis%20of%20confidence%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20discovers%20that%20her%20neighbor%2C%20at%20her%20father's%20secret%20lake%20house%20(long%20story)%2C%20is%20none%20other%20than%20Augustus%20%26quot%3BGus%26quot%3B%20Everett%2C%20a%20literary%20wunderkind%20and%20her%20former%20college%20classmate%2C%20January%20is%20inspired%20to%20begin%20writing%20again%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20not%20the%20contractually%20obligated%20romance%20she's%20supposed%20to%20be%20working%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJanuary%20and%20Gus%20bring%20out%20the%20best%20in%20each%20other.%20Gus%20makes%20January%20take%20herself%20seriously%2C%20and%20January%20lightens%20Gus%20up.%20They%20have%20great%20chemistry%2C%20believable%20issues%20that%20they%20work%20through%2C%20and%20a%20hard-won%20happily%20ever%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeach%20Read%26quot%3B%20is%20set%20to%20be%20adapted%20into%20a%20film%20directed%20by%20Yulin%20Kuang%2C%20a%20romance%20author%20in%20her%20own%20right%20%E2%80%94%20Kuang%20wrot